author: @sirynka
text: Javascript works perfectly without semicolons because js engine puts them without you but the re are few cases where you actually need to use them. One of the scenarios is when your next line is starting from bracket or curly bracket and if you will forget to put a semicolon browser will decide that this is the continue of the previous line of code and you will have an unexpected behavior from your program.
